      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> halved tomatoes</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 4-5 min further or until the tomatoes have broken down into a sauce</p><p>Once broken down, add your <strong>tomato stock</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1644835723579-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1644835723579-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1644835723579-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1644835723579-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1644835723579-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>spaghetti</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>spaghetti</strong> and reserve a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1644835730053-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
