          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1644835730053-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644835733403-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644835733403-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644835733403-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644835733403-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1644835733403-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> to the sauce with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped basil</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>crispy capers</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and give everything a good mix up until the sauce coats the pasta – this is your <strong>Amatriciana spaghetti</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644835738165-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644835738165-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644835738165-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644835738165-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1644835738165-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve your <strong>Amatriciana spaghetti</strong> and garnish with the <strong>remaining crispy capers</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>basil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
